\title{angle in a space-like wedge}
\author{trebor}
\import{common}
\taxon{Definition}

\p{
  Given a wedge formed by two vectors #{a} and #{b} contained in a space-like region, we define the angle as
  ##{
    \angle a b = \arcosh \frac{a \cdot b}{|a| \cdot |b|}.
  }
  Since #{\arcosh k = \ln (k + \sqrt{k^2 - 1})}, we can re-express it using the cross product:
  ##{
    \angle a b = \ln \frac{a \cdot b + |a \times b|}{|a| \cdot |b|}.
  }
}
